Section 1: Spring Core and Maven

Exercise 1: Configuring a Basic Spring Application
Description:
Sets up a simple Spring application with basic configuration using applicationContext.xml. Focuses on creating beans and using the Spring container to manage dependencies.

Exercise 2: Implementing Dependency Injection
Description:
Demonstrates Spring's Dependency Injection (DI) features including constructor-based and setter-based injection. This example helps understand how to decouple components in a Spring application.

Exercise 4: Creating and Configuring a Maven Project
Description:
Covers setting up a Spring project using Apache Maven for dependency management. Includes pom.xml configuration and integration of Spring libraries using Maven.


Section 2: Spring Data JPA with Spring Boot and Hibernate
Project: Spring Data JPA - Quick Example
Description:
A hands-on starter application demonstrating Spring Data JPA with Spring Boot. Includes basic repository setup, entity creation, and CRUD operations using JPA repositories.

Conceptual Exercise: Differences between JPA, Hibernate, and Spring Data JPA
Description:
A conceptual comparison between JPA, Hibernate, and Spring Data JPA. Helps in understanding how these technologies relate, differ, and integrate within a Spring Boot application.
